Many persons were feared killed as armed bandits attacked several communities in Dan Musa, Faskari and Batsari local governments areas of Katsina state. Multiple sources told our reporter that the bandits attacked the places while riding on motorcycles, killing several unsuspecting persons in the process. In Sabon Layin Galadima area of Faskari LGA, the bandits attacked at about dawn with locals putting the death at 11 persons. However, the police spokesman in the state, SP Gambo Isah, said information before the police showed that only one person was shot in his face adding that he is alive and receiving medical attention but admitted that animals were rustled with only one person injured too. Five persons were reportedly killed on Tuesday morning at Mara Zamfarawa village in Dan Musa LGA with many animals rustled. Locals say the bandits attacked farmers working on farmlands also. In Yar Gamji village of Batsari LGA, the bandits attacked on Tuesday afternoon as people run for safety. Locals say so far, ten persons have been killed. As at the time of filing this report, the police command is yet to respond to enquiries made on the other two incidences.  Details later… Many feared killed as armed bandits attack Bargaja community in Katsina How armed bandits unleash mayhem in Katsina villages Katsina: Residents of Batsari villages flee to council headquarters after bandits’ attacks Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin